<br>
Considering the setup required for a PA, I think CD should stun for longer, maybe even cause a little more damage.  The other 39+ crit styles should also be reviewed and likely altered, forget about all the evade triggered styles, give us something useful.<br>
<br>
Thrown weapon poisoning would be a big plus I think as well, even possibly being able to throw while running.<br>
<br>
On the subject of poisons, one thing that may not go by so well is the fact that other people's weapons can be poisoned for them.  I'd prefer to see be a skill that only we can use.  I have poisoned some weapons for people, but sometimes they go overboard asking for nearly 10 weapons poisoned.  I'd hate to be the one to face a melee wielding our deadliest poisons, it gives a melee quite an edge that I don't think was meant to be.  Oddly enough, when I gave a weapon I had in the bank to a shadowblade friend, a poison which was only 2 levels away from being able to use, wouldn't proc and I had to take it back, hit something with the weapon, for the proc to kick in and him to be able to poison the weapon himself.<br>
<br>
Envenom is one of our class defining skills, I'd like to keep it that way.  Maybe some kind of skill check when the poison procs?  Maybe cutting it to 1/4 usefulness if you don't have the proper skill?<br>
<br>
Also, concerning the enervating line of poisons....I'd prefer to see the poison changed to where it works similar to rezz effects, cutting the target's weaponskill.  Maybe even still debuffing constitution or possibly affecting endurance.  Something along those lines.<br>
<br>
Infiltrators complain many times about our 2h weapon capabilities, but I will tell you, yes the 2.5x is quite an advantage over our 2.2x, in my opinion.  Everytime I face an infiltrator (and there's rarely none who don't have at least 30 envenom on my server), my capability to fight them in melee is devasted by enervating line poisons which cut my str, thus cutting my weaponskill nearly in half sometimes.  Considering SB weapons are &quot;full str&quot; weapons, this hurts shadowblades very much against infiltrator and nightshade opponents.  Little good my 2h does me against them, unless I get my PA off, which against even con rarely happens.<br>
<br>
Maybe with a change to the enervating line, like I suggested above, would make this poison more effective against all classes, not so much the ones relying on str based weapons.<br>
